>
  <p>
    In a septic system full of large components — a tank, a field of buried trenches — the
    distribution box is easy to overlook. It's small, it's simple, and it has no moving parts. But it
    does a job that affects everything downstream of it, and when it goes wrong it can make a healthy
    drain field behave like a failing one. Understanding it can save you from assuming the most
    expensive diagnosis.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/septic-distribution-box-problems-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
